article.headline: Taylor doesn't miss from free-throw line (14-of-14)
article.linkText: Taylor's perfect effort enough for Santa Barbara
article.story:
SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Lindsay Taylor scored 18 points
including 14-of-14 from the free-throw line as  UC Santa
Barbara (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) beat UC Irvine 77-58 Thursday night.

	   Kristen Mann added 17 points and 10 rebounds for UC Santa
Barbara (14-3, 7-1 Big West Conference), who moved into first place
in the Big West after Long Beach State lost to Cal Poly San Luis
Obispo Thursday night.

	   Lauren Yadon of UC Irvine (11-7, 4-3) led all scorers with 20
points, making three-of-four three pointers. Christina Callaway
added 12 for the Anteaters.

	   Brandy Richardson led UC Santa Barbara with 11 rebounds as the
Gauchos out-rebounded UC Irvine 51-31.

	   Taylor made 12 of her free throws in the first half, leading
UCSB to a 35-22 lead at the break. The game was never close in the
second half.

	   Santa Barbara won its third-straight since losing its only
conference game of the season to Pacific on January 18. The Gauchos
have won nine of their last 10.
